content.description: Some fun moves broken up by a few scree filled ledges and a big bush. Crux comes half way up where there is a nice corner finger crack for 10-15 feet. Either climb the finger crack or do some stem moves with the corner on the right and a boulder feature on the left. Continue up wandering terrain and build an anchor, or walk off.
content.protection: A small assortment of cams and maybe a nut or two
content.location: 25 feet to the right of Deep Springs Education.

content.description:
This was actually a very fun and "sustained at the grade" route with decent rock for much of it. The crux is about 15 feet off the ground. If you go straight up the crack, it would probably be a solid mid 5.10 move. Or if you cheat around to the right for a couple of moves on a decent finger rail, the route goes at about 5.9.

Once achieving the ledge halfway up the route, do another reachy/cruxy move to get up where there is an obvious narrowing of two small angling roofs where you will climb between them in the narrow spot. Then do some crack/face climbing straight up to the rusty chains.
content.location: Dead middle of the formation up the obvious crack. See photo
